@@rThe Black Sun Shard@@N

@@dIn an age before dynasties, before the Keepers of Measure carved their first
obelisk, a fragment of something fell from the sky and struck the desert. It
was not fire. It was not stone. The priests who survived that era called it
@@ranti-light@@d: not darkness, which is merely the absence of light, but an
active force that consumes the properties light creates.@@N

@@eWhere sunlight reveals the world and makes it knowable, the Shard's
radiation makes things unknowable. Names dissolve. Histories contradict
themselves. The dead rise remembering lives they never lived. Crops fail
under clear skies. Entire households forget their own bloodlines and swear
loyalty to strangers who never existed.@@N

@@yPhysical reality remains intact. Buildings do not collapse. Rivers do not
reverse. But the narrative coherence of reality degrades. The Shard does not
attack bodies. It attacks meaning.@@N

@@dThis is why the Solar Court's response was institutional rather than
magical. You cannot fight anti-light with swords or spells. The only defense
the first kings found was to create institutions so robust, so deeply encoded
in stone and ritual and law, that meaning could be maintained by institutional
momentum even when individual memories failed.@@N

@@rThe Great Pyramid was raised as the Shard's prison, its reverse-solar
geometries binding the fragment through bureaucratic precision. Pharaoh
Ramesses accepted partial soul-binding to keep it dormant. The Northern
Pyramid was built as a backup containment ring. The Southern Pyramid was
built to descend toward its source and learn its grammar.@@N

@@eThe Keepers of Measure's obsessive record-keeping, the oasis Water Courts'
documented legal processes, the entire desert civilization's insistence on
encoding everything in stone: all of it was, at root, an anti-amnesia system
built to maintain coherence against the Shard's influence.@@N

@@yThe Umbral exist because of it: humanoids whose bodies have partially
incorporated the anti-light through long habitation in Shard-adjacent spaces.
The Shard's influence still leaks through degrading seals. It is the defining
cosmic threat of the world, contained but never defeated.@@N
